### Redis Sorted Sets & Leaderboard Operations
### Add players to game leaderboard
POST {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "member": "player1",
  "score": 1500
}

### Add more players
POST {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "member": "player2",
  "score": 2100
}

### Add another player
POST {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "member": "player3",
  "score": 1800
}

### Add more players for a complete leaderboard
POST {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "member": "player4",
  "score": 2500
}

### Add final player
POST {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "member": "player5",
  "score": 1200
}

### Get top 10 leaderboard (descending - highest scores first)
GET {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/leaderboard?count=10&descending=true

### Get top 3 leaderboard
GET {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/leaderboard?count=3&descending=true

### Get bottom performers (ascending - lowest scores first)
GET {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/leaderboard?count=3&descending=false

### Get specific player's rank
GET {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/rank/player2

### Get another player's rank
GET {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/rank/player5

### Check rank for non-existent player (should return 404)
GET {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/rank/nonexistent

### Update player score (higher score)
POST {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "member": "player1",
  "score": 2800
}

### Get updated leaderboard
GET {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/leaderboard?count=5&descending=true

### Check updated player rank
GET {{BaseUrl}}/sorted-sets/game:leaderboard/rank/player1
